comment: Mahinmi (WAS) sets the screen on Collison (SAC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Mahinmi (WAS) firms up his position and sets the screen on Collison (SAC).
Cauley-Stein (SAC) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Cauley-Stein (SAC) sets the screen on Bogdanovic (WAS) and the two players briefly engage and separate.
Wall (WAS) dislodges Collison (SAC) from his legal guarding position prior to the shot attempt.
[Observable in enhanced video] Collison (SAC) moves his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
Cauley-Stein (SAC) legally contests Wall's (WAS) jump shot attempt.
Afflalo (SAC) legally contests Bogdanovic's (WAS) jump shot attempt.
Correctly called 24 second violation.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor that Bogdanovic's (WAS) field goal attempt did not hit the rim stands.
[Observable in enhanced video] Afflalo (SAC) moves his pivot foot on the spin move.
Temple (SAC) makes marginal contact with Morris (WAS) on the shot attempt.
Wall (WAS) makes contact with the ball while defending Collison (SAC) on the perimeter.
Porter Jr. (WAS) makes incidental contact with Hield (SAC) that does not affect his SQBR.
Porter Jr. (WAS) blocks the shot attempt prior to the ball making contact with the backboard.
Cauley-Stein (SAC) is in the paint actively guarding an opponent following the screen set by Morris (WAS).
[Detectable with stop watch] Temple (SAC) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of WAS possession stands.
[Observable in enhanced video] Beal (WAS) moves his pivot foot on the spin move.
Correctly called 24 second violation.
Morris (WAS) obtains a legal guarding position and jumps vertically contesting the driving shot attempt by Collison (SAC).
Collison (SAC) commits a take foul on Beal (WAS).
Temple (SAC) commits a take foul on Beal (WAS).
Hield (SAC) commits a take foul on Morris (WAS).
